Business Brief -- AmBase Corp.:
   Capital Plan Is Approved
   For Carteret Savings Bank
AmBase declined to provide details about a private
placement, but the Carteret spokesman said the company would
like to complete a transaction by midyear. In a statement,
AmBase said it agreed that, at the discretion of the federal
Office of Thrift Supervision, if Carteret doesn't make
sufficient progress on its recapitalization, the OTS could
place it in its accelerated resolution program to preserve
Carteret's business.